Naming and lineage
------------------
Reasonledger is the standard first developed and documented under the name
AI-Native Notation (ANN). The earlier name is retained in the project history so
that the authorship and priority record remains continuous across the rename.


Open standard
-------------
Reasonledger is released as an open, royalty-free standard, intended to be freely
implementable by anyone, including in commercial products, under the licenses
above.


Patent
------
A US provisional patent application (63/980,973) was filed on 2026-02-12. The
decision whether to convert it to a non-provisional application before the
2026-02-12 deadline in 2027 is open. The specification and reference
implementation are published in this public repository and archived on Zenodo;
that public record documents the authorship and the date of public disclosure.


Development
-----------
Reasonledger was developed through human-directed work. The author conceived the
standard, specified the notation, designed the studies, and is responsible for
all content. A large language model (Claude, Anthropic) was used as an
instrument under the author's direction to assist with drafting, implementing the
author's specifications in code, and copy-editing. This is disclosed for
transparency and does not affect the licenses above.


Not a blockchain
----------------
"Ledger" refers to the auditable record the format produces across a reasoning
transfer chain. Reasonledger involves no distributed ledger, token, chain, or
consensus mechanism of any kind.
